s - es zeigt sich, dass schlussendlich vor allem Workers' Voice und Mitbestimmung zählen: Abhilfe ist nur möglich, wenn Missstände auch benannt werden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aArbeit. 4aArbeits- und Industriesoziologie. 4aArbeitsrecht. 4aArbeitsstandards. 4aCorporate Social Responsibility. 4aFirma. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aLieferkettengesetz. 4aMitbestimmung. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aSozialrecht. 4aSozialstandards. 4aSoziologie. 4aUnternehmen. 4aVerantwortung. 4aWorkers' Voice. 4aZivilgesellschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCivil Society.  aCodetermination.  aCorporate Social Responsibility.  aLabour Law.  aResponsibility.  aSocial Inequality.  aSociology of Work and Industry.  aSociology.  aWork.1 aCasey, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelaney, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobusch, Leonhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmons, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiedler, Antje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFulda, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGräf, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaipeter, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaipeter, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeimstädt, Maximilian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelfen, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4htt